WEBVTT

00:00.667 --> 00:02.667
             [♪♪♪]

00:21.421 --> 00:22.854
                  [YAWNS]

00:25.058 --> 00:27.459
   Oh, good morning, master.

00:27.461 --> 00:28.460
I am sorry.

00:28.462 --> 00:29.461
I must have overslept.

00:29.463 --> 00:30.462
          Good morning, Jeannie.

00:30.464 --> 00:31.463
    [GASPS]

00:31.465 --> 00:33.598
You made breakfast
all by yourself.

00:33.600 --> 00:34.599
                [CHUCKLES]

00:34.601 --> 00:36.535
Oh, how clever of you.

00:36.537 --> 00:38.836
              Oh, help yourself.

00:38.838 --> 00:40.138
Is there any mail for me?

00:40.140 --> 00:42.407
  Who would be writing to you?

00:42.409 --> 00:46.812
Oh, Omar Khayyám, Julius Caesar.

00:46.814 --> 00:50.982
       Oh. No, I'm sorry.
   It seems to be all for me.

00:50.984 --> 00:52.016
Oh, here's a reminder

00:52.018 --> 00:54.285
about the television show
tomorrow night.

00:54.287 --> 00:55.554
      What show is that, master?

00:55.556 --> 00:57.755
      Oh, uh, once a year
  the American Air Force bases

00:57.757 --> 00:59.424
       all over the world
     put on a talent show.

00:59.426 --> 01:01.893
 They-- they pick a contestant
        from each base.

01:01.895 --> 01:03.061
                 Oh, that sounds
                    exciting.

01:03.063 --> 01:04.363
             Mm-hm.

01:04.364 --> 01:06.965
     Oh, they're gonna beam
      the show on Telstar.

01:06.967 --> 01:09.234
   They'll have, uh, someone
    broadcasting from Alaska

01:09.236 --> 01:11.903
      and Hawaii and here
        at Cape Kennedy.

01:11.905 --> 01:13.038
   The winner gets a trophy.

01:13.040 --> 01:15.874
    Oh, good. We will put it
         on the mantel.

01:15.876 --> 01:17.109
   What are you going to do?

01:17.111 --> 01:20.178
         I'm gonna sit
  in the audience to applaud.

01:20.180 --> 01:22.047
      Oh, but you must be
        in the contest.

01:22.049 --> 01:23.882
          [CHUCKLING]
     Well, what would I do?

01:23.884 --> 01:26.284
     Well, does it matter?

01:26.286 --> 01:27.619
     Well, yeah, a little.

01:27.621 --> 01:29.187
   Well, you can do anything.

01:29.189 --> 01:31.957
   Uh, no, no, Jeannie.
   You can do anything,

01:31.959 --> 01:33.625
        And don't.

01:33.627 --> 01:35.360
              Oh, but the mantel
                needs a trophy.

01:35.362 --> 01:37.529
Well, blink one in. I'm not
gonna be in that contest.

01:37.531 --> 01:38.897
            I know you can sing.

01:38.899 --> 01:40.799
        [CHUCKLING]
Have you ever heard me sing?

01:40.801 --> 01:42.634
               Oh, yes. You have
              a beautiful voice.

01:42.636 --> 01:43.635
Oh, come on, Jeannie.

01:43.637 --> 01:44.703
         Sing something, master.

01:44.705 --> 01:46.471
Oh, come on. No, no.
             Oh, please, please.

01:46.473 --> 01:48.740
   Sing something from the opera
         we saw last night.

01:48.742 --> 01:50.042
What,<i> Rigoletto?</i>
                    Mm-hm.

01:50.044 --> 01:51.910
      Really?
                   Uh-huh.

01:51.912 --> 01:52.911
   Okay, why not.

01:52.913 --> 01:54.046
         [BOTH CHUCKLE]

01:54.048 --> 01:56.247
  [CLEARS THROAT]

01:56.249 --> 01:58.249
  [WARBLES VERDI'S
"LA DONNA È MOBILE"]

02:01.622 --> 02:03.321
Yeah, well, that's--
     That's it.

02:03.323 --> 02:04.623
   Oh, that's beautiful, master.

02:04.625 --> 02:05.691
       Yeah?
                  [GIGGLES]

02:05.693 --> 02:06.692
            Sing something else.

02:06.694 --> 02:07.826
       Uh...
                   Please.

02:07.828 --> 02:09.294
   All right, um,
why don't I try a--?

02:09.295 --> 02:10.762
A light scale, hm?
         Mm-hm. Mm-hm.

02:13.234 --> 02:14.766
   [IN KEY]
♪ La, la, la ♪

02:14.768 --> 02:15.967
    ♪ La, laaa ♪

02:15.969 --> 02:21.306
♪ Laaaa, laaaa, laaaaa ♪

02:23.877 --> 02:26.043
   [STAMMERING]
 Did you see that?

02:26.045 --> 02:29.213
                 Saw it,
         but I don't believe it.

02:29.215 --> 02:31.216
             [♪♪♪]

02:34.120 --> 02:36.120
             [♪♪♪]

03:23.169 --> 03:25.169
             [♪♪♪]

03:30.109 --> 03:32.210
   [STAMMERING]
Well, good morning,
   Dr. Bellows.

03:32.212 --> 03:35.413
  Major, uh, where did you learn
        to sing like that?

03:35.415 --> 03:36.914
   Oh, it's a--
   It's a gift.

03:36.916 --> 03:38.282
              Oh, I've heard you
                 sing before,

03:38.284 --> 03:41.118
             but it didn't sound
             anything like this.

03:41.120 --> 03:44.556
Well, you know what they say.
Practice makes perfect.

03:44.558 --> 03:46.391
    BELLOWS:
Uh, Major Nelson.

03:46.393 --> 03:49.494
     Do you mind letting me hear
          that voice again?

03:49.496 --> 03:50.796
Uh, I'd really rather not, sir.

03:50.798 --> 03:52.497
You see, the strain
in the morning air--

03:52.499 --> 03:53.665
               Just a few notes.

03:53.667 --> 03:54.866
      TONY:
If you don't mind,

03:54.868 --> 03:56.735
       I'd, uh-- Why not.

04:00.841 --> 04:02.774
    [CRESCENDOING]
♪ La, la, la, la, la ♪

04:02.776 --> 04:04.209
♪ La, la, la, laaaaa ♪

04:13.787 --> 04:15.653
                  Fantastic.

04:15.655 --> 04:17.221
  Yes, I think you
might say that, sir.

04:17.223 --> 04:18.857
        Is there anything
        I can do for you?

04:18.858 --> 04:23.094
      Well, um, I had some forms
         for you to fill out,

04:23.096 --> 04:27.732
but, uh, with a voice like that,
  you mustn't waste your time.

04:29.570 --> 04:31.670
    I'll see you later, major.

04:31.672 --> 04:33.672
             [♪♪♪]

04:35.875 --> 04:36.874
      [SNICKERS]

04:38.679 --> 04:40.545
         ♪ Ahhhhh ♪

04:40.547 --> 04:42.046
         [GLASS CRACKS]

04:50.257 --> 04:51.989
             Fantastic.

04:56.430 --> 04:57.562
         [GIGGLING]

04:59.333 --> 05:01.233
What am I doing?

05:01.235 --> 05:02.433
   Jeannie.

05:02.435 --> 05:03.568
                [JEANNIE LAUGHS]

05:03.570 --> 05:04.569
       Jeannie.

05:04.571 --> 05:07.605
       Oh, yes, master.

05:07.607 --> 05:09.607
I'd like to speak to you.

05:13.413 --> 05:15.313
                    Yes, master.

05:15.315 --> 05:16.548
         No.

05:16.550 --> 05:17.615
                     No, what?

05:17.617 --> 05:19.183
No, I'm not gonna be
  in that contest.

05:19.185 --> 05:20.485
               Oh, but you must.

05:20.487 --> 05:23.354
        How will I look if some
      other genie's master wins?

05:23.356 --> 05:25.557
     Well, I doubt
if that'll ever come up.

05:25.559 --> 05:27.158
 Now, just forget
about the contest.

05:27.160 --> 05:28.726
          If you say so, master.

05:28.728 --> 05:30.294
Oh, no you don't.
Oh, no you don't.

05:30.296 --> 05:32.063
You're gonna blink
 that voice away,

05:32.065 --> 05:33.731
or I won't forgive you.

05:33.733 --> 05:35.433
   I swear.
                But it is such
               a lovely voice--

05:35.435 --> 05:37.335
Ah, no, ah-ah, Jeannie.
 No, I'm not kidding.

05:37.337 --> 05:38.336
                   But--
        No.

05:38.338 --> 05:40.071
                   Plea--
       Mm.

05:40.073 --> 05:42.006
              Very well, master.

05:42.008 --> 05:45.242
I promise that you will not sing
       like Caruso again.

05:45.244 --> 05:46.711
     Wait.
                     Hm?

05:48.949 --> 05:53.417
  ♪ Goodbye ♪

05:55.455 --> 05:56.454
   All right.

05:59.593 --> 06:01.593
[SINGS NOTES OFF-KEY]

06:04.330 --> 06:06.865
     And that makes you happier?

06:06.867 --> 06:09.433
 No, it just makes
me feel a lot safer.

06:09.435 --> 06:11.035
Usually, when you do
   these things,

06:11.037 --> 06:12.570
I get into a lot
  of trouble.

06:12.572 --> 06:15.172
 Luckily, this time there's--
There's been no trouble, and--

06:15.174 --> 06:16.841
Well, if you promise
not to do it again,

06:16.843 --> 06:18.610
  we'll just forget
about the whole thing.

06:18.612 --> 06:20.545
                Yes, master. Oh.
                   Oh, master.

06:20.547 --> 06:22.513
  When will Major Healey return?

06:22.515 --> 06:24.448
Uh, he oughta be back
tomorrow. Look at this.

06:24.450 --> 06:26.617
  Oh, good. Then I will find out
       when my birthday is.

06:26.619 --> 06:28.386
   Yeah, I-- I've got
to get back to the base.

06:28.388 --> 06:30.588
Would you clean up all this
glass and that stuff, huh?

06:30.590 --> 06:32.190
          Oh, certainly, master.

06:32.859 --> 06:34.125
                      [SIGHS]

06:34.127 --> 06:35.860
        I'll see you later.

06:35.862 --> 06:37.695
                    Mm. Bye-bye.
        Goodbye.

06:37.697 --> 06:39.697
             [♪♪♪]

06:44.037 --> 06:45.770
             Caruso?

06:45.772 --> 06:49.140
              Tony Nelson's got
            a voice like Caruso?

06:49.142 --> 06:51.609
That's right, general.
  I heard it myself.

06:51.611 --> 06:53.178
                Now, that's hard
                   to believe.

06:53.180 --> 06:56.347
 Well, general. No one's
more surprised than I am.

06:56.349 --> 06:58.416
I don't know what happened,
     but as you know,

06:58.418 --> 06:59.684
  I'm somewhat
of an opera bug.

06:59.686 --> 07:00.751
                        Yeah.

07:00.753 --> 07:02.654
And I'm telling you,
Major Nelson has one

07:02.656 --> 07:04.489
of the greatest voices
   I've ever heard.

07:04.491 --> 07:06.491
         And you think he oughta
          represent Cape Kennedy

07:06.493 --> 07:08.959
         on that television show
             tomorrow night?

07:08.961 --> 07:10.795
I've already entered him.

07:10.797 --> 07:12.063
We can't lose.

07:12.065 --> 07:13.665
          Well, you oughta know.

07:13.667 --> 07:16.534
                Boy, I'd like
             to get that trophy.

07:16.536 --> 07:19.604
       It would look awful good.
           Up on the mantel.

07:19.606 --> 07:20.838
          In the Officers' Club.

07:20.840 --> 07:22.473
That's what I thought, general.

07:22.475 --> 07:24.475
              What did Tony say?

07:24.477 --> 07:26.744
Oh, I haven't told him yet.
Oh, but he'll be thrilled.

07:26.746 --> 07:29.480
After all, it's quite an honor
to represent the space center.

07:29.482 --> 07:30.681
                  Yeah...

07:31.885 --> 07:34.252
      Oh, I want to see his face
          when you tell him.

07:34.254 --> 07:35.987
            [LAUGHS]

07:35.989 --> 07:37.722
           [LAUGHING]

07:37.724 --> 07:39.024
        You entered me in what?

07:39.026 --> 07:40.792
           PETERSON:
 I knew you'd be pleased, Tony.

07:40.794 --> 07:43.161
 Oh, sir. I can't sing, general.
     I really-- I can't sing.

07:43.163 --> 07:45.897
I admire your modesty, major,
but in this case, believe me,

07:45.899 --> 07:47.198
it's misplaced.

07:47.200 --> 07:49.767
You have a voice that even
Caruso would have been proud of.

07:49.769 --> 07:51.269
  Yeah, he was. Well, I mean--

07:51.271 --> 07:52.971
       You're gonna have
     to find somebody else

07:52.973 --> 07:54.339
to represent Cape Kennedy, sir.

07:54.341 --> 07:55.673
       Well, I don't understand.

07:55.675 --> 07:58.043
    I thought you'd be proud
to be up there, giving your all.

07:58.045 --> 07:59.945
     Well, that's just it,
    it's not my all to give.

07:59.947 --> 08:01.246
Major, you have
the only voice

08:01.248 --> 08:03.181
I've ever heard
that shatters glass.

08:03.183 --> 08:04.215
                    He did that?

08:04.217 --> 08:05.216
More than once. I saw it.

08:05.218 --> 08:06.884
          [STAMMERING]
    It was an accident, sir.

08:06.886 --> 08:07.885
       Just an accident.

08:07.887 --> 08:09.387
        Uh, believe me,
      if I went out there,

08:09.389 --> 08:11.056
         I'd be singing
     under false pretenses.

08:11.058 --> 08:12.357
                  Why would you?

08:12.359 --> 08:14.392
     Well, I-- I don't have
     a trained voice, sir.

08:14.394 --> 08:15.793
          I don't have
      any control over it.

08:15.795 --> 08:17.662
      Sometimes it works,
     sometimes it doesn't.

08:17.664 --> 08:19.364
       Tony, I have my heart set
            on this trophy.

08:19.366 --> 08:21.833
   Now, you're gonna go in and
 you're going to win, aren't ya?

08:21.835 --> 08:22.834
           Well, I--
            [SNAPS]

08:22.836 --> 08:23.969
          Uh... The--

08:23.971 --> 08:25.971
           [SNEEZES]

08:25.973 --> 08:28.373
 I've had this cold coming on.
  I feel it's gonna get worse.

08:28.375 --> 08:30.141
       We can't let that happen,
            can we, doctor?

08:30.143 --> 08:31.809
Oh, no.
                 You go home
            and take care of it.

08:31.811 --> 08:32.943
         Oh, well, I--

08:32.946 --> 08:34.812
        I want you in good shape
           for tomorrow night.

08:34.813 --> 08:36.414
 Yes, sir, I'll--
I'll certainly try.

08:36.416 --> 08:38.116
I-- I--

08:40.687 --> 08:42.386
It's all right,
  thank you.

08:43.991 --> 08:45.256
[TONY SNEEZES]

09:03.076 --> 09:04.375
           [SNEEZES]

09:04.377 --> 09:07.178
        Oh, good, good.
          Cold, good!

09:07.180 --> 09:09.147
Master, your dinner is ready.

09:09.149 --> 09:10.148
Do you want it--?

09:14.754 --> 09:16.253
     What are you doing, master?

09:16.255 --> 09:17.455
Committing suicide.

09:17.457 --> 09:19.524
  But you could catch your death
        of cold like that.

09:19.526 --> 09:20.692
  That's the idea.

09:20.694 --> 09:21.793
     Oh, well, you did not think

09:21.795 --> 09:23.495
               I would let you
            catch cold, did you?

09:23.497 --> 09:24.896
      Jeannie,
you don't understand.

09:24.898 --> 09:25.964
I'm trying to catch cold.

09:25.966 --> 09:28.165
                 Oh, I could not
                let you do that.

09:31.738 --> 09:33.905
     As long as I am your genie,

09:33.907 --> 09:38.009
         you are going to remain
            in perfect health.

09:38.011 --> 09:39.043
                   Oh.

09:40.547 --> 09:42.079
      [SHOUTING]

09:43.750 --> 09:44.749
       Ow!

09:46.519 --> 09:50.020
           [HOARSELY]
   "And so, my fellow members
          of Congress,

09:50.022 --> 09:54.625
   "I say that on this great
  and glorious Fourth of July,

09:54.627 --> 09:58.162
     "we should commemorate
the magnificent pioneer spirits

09:58.164 --> 10:01.031
      "of those who blazed
       the trail for us,

10:01.033 --> 10:03.601
       those who sent us
  on the march to victory..."

10:03.603 --> 10:05.236
                         Master?
         Hm?

10:05.238 --> 10:07.405
              Master, it is 3:00
                in the morning.

10:07.407 --> 10:08.606
             What are you doing?

10:08.608 --> 10:10.207
I-- I'm just reading
     a little.

10:10.209 --> 10:11.442
       Your voice sounds hoarse.

10:11.444 --> 10:13.444
  Does it? Yeah, oh, no,
I feel fine. You go to bed.

10:13.446 --> 10:14.612
    You sure you feel all right?

10:14.614 --> 10:15.613
    [CHUCKLING]

10:15.615 --> 10:17.948
I never felt better
    in my life.

10:17.950 --> 10:19.384
     [CLEARS THROAT]

10:19.386 --> 10:22.152
"In 1776, when our brave
    forefathers took

10:22.154 --> 10:25.723
"this first magnificent step
      towards liberty

10:25.725 --> 10:27.291
"and went into battle,

10:27.293 --> 10:30.595
"it was because they heard the
voices of the oppressed crying,

10:30.597 --> 10:32.563
    [NORMAL VOICE]
       'Help.'"

10:32.565 --> 10:33.798
       [GROANS]

10:38.605 --> 10:41.672
      Help. Help. Help.

10:41.674 --> 10:43.674
             [♪♪♪]

10:48.347 --> 10:49.714
                      Jeannie.
         [MAGIC BOINGS]

10:51.017 --> 10:52.216
Good morning, master.

10:52.218 --> 10:53.584
        [CHUCKLING]
     Oh, good morning.

10:53.586 --> 10:55.386
Did you sleep well?

10:55.388 --> 10:57.154
      No, as a matter
     of fact, I didn't.

10:57.156 --> 10:59.189
       I didn't close
  my eyes once last night.

10:59.191 --> 11:01.092
        Spent the whole night
        coming to a decision.

11:01.094 --> 11:02.093
              Oh...

11:02.095 --> 11:04.662
      What decision was that,
              master?

11:04.664 --> 11:08.766
   Well, I decided that since
I can't get out of the contest,

11:08.768 --> 11:10.200
   I might as well go in
        and win it.

11:10.202 --> 11:11.502
       [CHUCKLING]
       That's nice.

11:13.806 --> 11:15.806
       Thank you, master.

11:15.808 --> 11:18.443
   As a matter of fact, I kind
 of enjoyed singing like Caruso.

11:18.445 --> 11:19.610
           [SNICKERS]

11:19.612 --> 11:20.611
            Did you?

11:20.613 --> 11:21.612
               Mm-hm.

11:21.614 --> 11:23.381
      As a matter of fact,

11:23.383 --> 11:24.581
I think the trophy
    oughta go

11:25.185 --> 11:26.317
              right here.

11:26.319 --> 11:28.853
Oh, perhaps a nice vase
would be better, master.

11:31.657 --> 11:32.656
Who needs a vase

11:32.658 --> 11:33.691
     when I have a trophy?

11:34.894 --> 11:36.560
           [OFF-KEY]
     ♪ La, la, la, laaaaa ♪

11:36.562 --> 11:37.996
♪ Laaaaaa ♪

11:39.833 --> 11:42.500
         Oh, thank you.

11:42.502 --> 11:44.101
        Ahem.

11:44.103 --> 11:45.503
    [CLEARS THROAT]

11:45.505 --> 11:48.305
Wouldn't they be surprised if
I sang like that tonight, huh?

11:48.307 --> 11:50.174
         [BOTH CHUCKLE]

11:50.176 --> 11:51.375
Okay, go ahead.

11:51.377 --> 11:52.844
                 Go ahead?

11:52.846 --> 11:55.680
   Yeah, you know, uh,
    blink in Caruso.

11:55.682 --> 11:56.681
                       No.

11:56.683 --> 11:57.682
       No, what?

11:57.684 --> 11:58.917
                No, master?

11:58.919 --> 12:00.584
     Jeannie, I want
   to sing like Caruso.

12:00.586 --> 12:02.253
              Thou canst not.

12:02.255 --> 12:03.888
 Who said I canst not?

12:03.890 --> 12:05.924
          You did. Oh, remember?

12:05.926 --> 12:07.825
          You made me promise
       that you would never sing

12:07.827 --> 12:10.194
        like Caruso again,
  or you would never forgive me.

12:10.196 --> 12:11.562
          Don't listen
      to what I told you,

12:11.564 --> 12:12.830
 listen to what I'm telling ya.

12:12.832 --> 12:14.231
           Oh, I knew you were
              yelling at me.

12:14.233 --> 12:16.233
Yelling at you? This is
a whisper compared to--

12:16.235 --> 12:17.735
               If you want me,
            I will be shopping--

12:17.737 --> 12:19.470
      Shopping? Jeannie--
                     In Baghdad.

12:19.472 --> 12:20.905
      Don't do this to me.

12:20.907 --> 12:22.773
            Jeannie!

12:22.775 --> 12:24.943
            Now, come on! Naaah!

12:24.945 --> 12:26.110
              Listen, you see--

12:26.112 --> 12:27.678
               Ahh, ahh, ahh.

12:27.680 --> 12:30.215
            [SINGS NOTE OFF-KEY]

12:30.217 --> 12:31.850
                   Jeannie.

12:38.491 --> 12:41.159
                 [OFF-KEY]
                ♪ Naaaaaaa ♪

12:43.129 --> 12:45.463
                ♪ Oooaahh ♪

12:47.500 --> 12:48.632
                    Ah!

12:48.634 --> 12:50.501
              What is it--?
        Oh, when'd you get back?

12:50.503 --> 12:51.502
Couple of minutes ago.

12:51.504 --> 12:53.104
Uh, what are you trying
    to do, anyway?

12:53.106 --> 12:54.172
       I'm trying to break that.

12:54.174 --> 12:55.273
You can't break that?
                         No.

12:55.275 --> 12:56.507
Would you like some help?

12:56.509 --> 12:57.508
            You think you could?

12:58.544 --> 12:59.977
             [♪♪♪]

13:03.182 --> 13:05.182
             [♪♪♪]

13:05.184 --> 13:06.417
                     Thanks.

13:06.419 --> 13:07.484
    Forget it.

13:07.486 --> 13:08.986
   Hey, listen, uh,
   where's Jeannie?

13:08.988 --> 13:10.687
  I'd like to tell her
  about her birthday.

13:10.689 --> 13:13.090
She went shopping.
               Shopping!

13:13.092 --> 13:14.358
       Yeah.

13:14.360 --> 13:16.327
  Hey, look, why don't
we get dressed up tonight

13:16.329 --> 13:17.528
and have a celebration, huh?

13:17.530 --> 13:18.796
                   I'm sorry.
               I'm busy tonight.

13:18.798 --> 13:21.065
Oh, doing what?
    I think you better sit down.

13:21.067 --> 13:22.333
I don't wanna sit down.

13:22.335 --> 13:24.302
          I'm singing in
  the Air Force contest tonight.

13:24.304 --> 13:26.003
You're singing in the--
                   That's right.

13:26.005 --> 13:27.638
Why don't I sit down?
                        Mm-hmm.

13:29.442 --> 13:30.641
You're sing--?

13:30.643 --> 13:33.344
You're singing in a contest
     with your voice?

13:33.346 --> 13:35.480
     No, originally it was
     somebody else's voice.

13:35.482 --> 13:37.148
        Now, you may find
      this hard to believe,

13:37.150 --> 13:38.816
       but yesterday I sang
        a lot like Caruso.

13:38.818 --> 13:40.251
   Now or when he was living?

13:41.420 --> 13:43.121
                Oh, I'm serious.

13:43.123 --> 13:44.122
             Jeannie.

13:44.124 --> 13:45.189
       Jeannie?
                   That's right.

13:45.191 --> 13:46.958
Jeannie gave you
Caruso's voice?

13:46.960 --> 13:48.626
   Well, maybe she changed it
          back again.

13:48.628 --> 13:49.994
 Why don't you sing something.

13:49.996 --> 13:51.562
        Ahem. All right.

13:51.564 --> 13:53.231
        [WARBLES VERDI'S
      "LA DONNA È MOBILE"]

13:53.233 --> 13:55.366
            [CRYING]

13:55.368 --> 13:56.534
           I'm desperate, Roger.

13:56.536 --> 13:58.602
    If I don't sing tonight,
        General Peterson

13:58.604 --> 14:01.005
and Dr. Bellows are gonna think
     I'm letting 'em down.

14:01.007 --> 14:02.773
         And if you do sing,
          you'll by lynched.

14:02.775 --> 14:04.442
            Do you realize
       about 30 million people

14:04.444 --> 14:06.210
        are gonna be watching
          that show tonight?

14:06.212 --> 14:08.112
        They'll probably laugh
         themselves to death.

14:08.114 --> 14:09.380
           Thanks. Thanks, Roge.

14:09.382 --> 14:10.982
             I needed a friend
           like you to come back

14:10.984 --> 14:13.318
     from the Arctic and tell me
     really honest and straight.

14:13.320 --> 14:16.287
Wait a minute, wait a minute,
You don't have to sing tonight.

14:16.289 --> 14:18.622
Oh, you don't have to sing.

14:18.624 --> 14:20.591
   I just solved
your whole problem.

14:20.593 --> 14:22.393
                     What?
       Oh, catch cold.

14:22.395 --> 14:23.394
                 Catch cold.

14:23.396 --> 14:24.528
    Catch cold.

14:24.530 --> 14:26.530
   All you have to do
is take off your clothes,

14:26.532 --> 14:29.367
 stand in front of an open
window with the fan on you,

14:29.369 --> 14:31.235
put your feet in a tub
    of ice water!

14:31.237 --> 14:32.236
     I'm out of ice cubes.

14:32.238 --> 14:34.505
             I already tried it.

14:34.507 --> 14:38.709
    You're out of ice cubes
   and you didn't catch cold.

14:38.711 --> 14:39.944
    Jeannie wouldn't let me.

14:42.682 --> 14:44.515
         Wait a minute.

14:44.517 --> 14:47.184
       Oh, are you lucky
    to have me for a friend.

14:47.186 --> 14:48.519
                     What?
Look at this.

14:48.521 --> 14:50.888
 Now, just read out loud
at the top of your voice,

14:50.890 --> 14:52.489
and I guarantee you

14:52.491 --> 14:54.358
           within one hour,
        your throat will be--

14:54.360 --> 14:55.359
             Cut.

14:55.361 --> 14:56.360
             You tried it?

14:57.397 --> 14:58.395
                Tony...

14:59.098 --> 15:00.398
           You got a problem.

15:00.400 --> 15:01.565
            Yes.

15:03.036 --> 15:06.670
   Oh, boy. Why can't Jeannie
make you sing like Caruso again?

15:06.672 --> 15:08.639
  Because one of the greatest
       minds of our time

15:08.641 --> 15:10.341
    made her promise not to.

15:13.012 --> 15:15.112
Well, what do you
     do now?

15:15.114 --> 15:16.547
               I don't know.
               I don't know.

15:16.549 --> 15:19.650
   Do I--? Do I throw myself on
  the mercy of General Peterson,

15:19.652 --> 15:22.986
                or do I jump
            in front of a truck?

15:22.988 --> 15:24.955
       Jump in front of a truck.

15:27.026 --> 15:29.693
      PETERSON:
Seventy, 80, 90, 100.

15:29.695 --> 15:30.962
                   I feel guilty
                    about this.

15:30.964 --> 15:32.263
                 I should really
                  give you odds.

15:32.265 --> 15:33.564
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

15:33.566 --> 15:35.632
   Come in.

15:35.634 --> 15:37.434
Oh, I'm sorry--
         Oh, Tony.

15:37.436 --> 15:38.535
     Come on in, Tony.

15:38.537 --> 15:39.904
     We were just talking
          about you.

15:39.906 --> 15:41.405
Oh, uh, just talking
about me, sir?

15:41.407 --> 15:43.574
     This is General Brill
  from Edwards Air Force Base.

15:43.576 --> 15:44.575
     This is Major Nelson.

15:44.577 --> 15:45.576
Oh, how do you do, sir?

15:45.578 --> 15:47.312
                 So this is
            "The Golden Thrush."

15:47.314 --> 15:48.879
      "The Golden Thrush."

15:48.881 --> 15:50.881
                  PETERSON:
             Yeah, I was telling
                him about you.

15:50.883 --> 15:53.150
 As a matter of fact,
I just bet $100 on it.

15:53.152 --> 15:55.619
       A hundred dollars?
    Well, $100 is nothing--

15:55.621 --> 15:57.622
     You're right.
You want to make it 200?

15:57.624 --> 15:59.223
                      You're on.

15:59.225 --> 16:00.391
  I was telling General Brill

16:00.393 --> 16:01.892
          he's in for
    a big surprise tonight.

16:01.894 --> 16:03.161
  Yes.

16:03.163 --> 16:05.896
You think we oughta give him
a little sample, or, uh...?

16:05.898 --> 16:07.164
Shall we save our ammunition?

16:07.166 --> 16:09.100
       I think we oughta
      save our ammunition.

16:09.102 --> 16:10.101
            Right.

16:10.103 --> 16:11.102
[PHONE RINGS]

16:11.104 --> 16:12.103
           Excuse me.
  Yes.

16:14.006 --> 16:15.172
                    Yeah.

16:15.174 --> 16:17.274
              What? What!

16:17.944 --> 16:19.143
Well, if you tell them,

16:19.145 --> 16:20.945
  if they're not able
to do the job properly,

16:20.947 --> 16:23.580
they're not fit to be officers
representing this command!

16:23.582 --> 16:25.883
     And I, personally, will see
       that they're transferred

16:25.885 --> 16:27.118
          to duties elsewhere!

16:29.055 --> 16:30.654
Ah, Tony, my boy.

16:30.656 --> 16:33.357
That trophy's gonna look
wonderful sitting up there

16:33.359 --> 16:35.359
on the mantel
in the Officers' Club.

16:35.361 --> 16:39.196
Or else you're gonna have a very
unhappy general on your hands.

16:39.198 --> 16:41.799
[LAUGHS]

16:41.801 --> 16:43.801
         [ALL LAUGHING]

16:43.803 --> 16:46.303
     Yes. Well, if you gentlemen
       will excuse me, please.

16:46.305 --> 16:47.304
Off to rehearse?

16:47.306 --> 16:49.039
                  Uh, no, sir,
                to find a truck.

16:49.041 --> 16:50.775
          [BOTH LAUGH]

16:56.482 --> 16:58.482
      [TOOTHBRUSH BUZZING]

16:58.484 --> 17:00.484
         [HUMS]

17:03.422 --> 17:05.422
       [SINGS IN ITALIAN]

17:06.959 --> 17:08.425
       [SIGHS]

17:08.426 --> 17:11.028
I wonder why they didn't ask me
to sing in that contest tonight?

17:11.030 --> 17:12.496
                I wish they had.

17:12.498 --> 17:14.364
Oh, hi, uh, have you heard
from Jeannie yet?

17:14.366 --> 17:16.500
            No, but I've heard
          from General Peterson.

17:16.502 --> 17:19.336
          Roge, we're gonna have
           an accident tonight.

17:19.338 --> 17:21.305
Hey, I think you've had
an accident already.

17:21.307 --> 17:23.339
  No, no. I mean, we're gonna
       fake an accident.

17:23.342 --> 17:24.942
We're gonna go up
to the country club

17:24.944 --> 17:26.443
for dinner tonight,
and on the way,

17:26.444 --> 17:28.612
we're gonna have a flat tire
or, uh, bump a tree or--

17:28.614 --> 17:30.915
    Oh, I get it. You don't have
    to show up at the broadcast,

17:30.917 --> 17:31.916
          and nobody blames you.

17:31.918 --> 17:33.284
                  Good thinking.
   That's right.

17:33.286 --> 17:34.651
         There's only one thing.
        What?

17:34.653 --> 17:36.053
             We'll use your car.

17:36.055 --> 17:37.121
      Oh, gentlemen.
Oh, hi.

17:37.123 --> 17:38.122
  I'm glad I caught you.

17:38.124 --> 17:39.389
                      Caught us?
Caught us?

17:39.391 --> 17:41.792
Uh, yes. Have you made any plans
    for dinner this evening?

17:41.794 --> 17:43.994
Well, yes, we're going out
to the country club, sir.

17:43.996 --> 17:45.996
         Yeah, they have a lot
      of accidents on that road.

17:45.998 --> 17:47.798
      Oh, why don't we all
     have dinner together?

17:47.800 --> 17:49.566
The three of us?
              Yes.

17:49.568 --> 17:50.901
                     Uh, no, no.
  Roge.

17:50.903 --> 17:52.970
  Uh, yes. Then we can go back
     to your house with you

17:52.972 --> 17:55.372
while you change, and then we'll
   escort you to the studio.

17:55.374 --> 17:56.740
    Oh.
   We wouldn't want anything

17:56.742 --> 17:59.210
   to happen to you tonight,
    would we, Major Nelson?

17:59.212 --> 18:00.811
            BELLOWS:
          Shall we go?

18:00.813 --> 18:02.313
             [♪♪♪]

18:03.816 --> 18:05.649
            Come on.
I'd just be in the way!

18:14.026 --> 18:15.826
 Now, Major Nelson,
during the rehearsal,

18:15.828 --> 18:18.428
I want you to--
 Major Nelson.

18:18.430 --> 18:19.429
                         Yes--
                       Yes, sir.

18:19.431 --> 18:20.697
 Hey, look at all this, anyway.

18:20.699 --> 18:22.099
          I feel like I'm
         in show business.

18:22.101 --> 18:24.068
Oh, uh, Mr. Hennessy.
Uh, just a moment.

18:25.771 --> 18:27.471
Uh, this is Major Nelson.
               How do you do?

18:27.473 --> 18:29.273
And Major Healey.
         Sir.

18:29.275 --> 18:31.375
Uh, Mr. Hennessy will be
your accompanist.

18:31.377 --> 18:32.410
 I was getting worried.

18:32.412 --> 18:34.111
  Well, I'm sorry we're late.

18:34.113 --> 18:36.280
     We had two flat tires

18:36.282 --> 18:39.383
and almost hit a tree.

18:39.385 --> 18:41.285
 Um, I'm afraid we aren't
   gonna have any time

18:41.287 --> 18:42.953
   to rehearse, major.

18:42.955 --> 18:45.389
         You probably don't have
             my music anyway.

18:45.391 --> 18:47.825
   You told me he sang opera.

18:47.827 --> 18:50.394
   Well, I can play the arias
  from any opera ever written.

18:50.396 --> 18:52.596
     Wagner, Verdi, Bizet.
  What would you like to sing?

18:52.598 --> 18:54.465
                  Do you know
              "Melancholy Baby"?

18:55.267 --> 18:56.634
          "Melancholy Baby"?

18:56.636 --> 18:57.634
   [LAUGHS]

18:57.636 --> 18:59.303
Good old Tony,
always kidding around.

19:00.739 --> 19:02.739
   Gentlemen, we only have
   a short amount of time.

19:02.741 --> 19:04.441
     Now, how 'bout doing
     "La donna è mobile"

19:04.443 --> 19:05.809
        from <i> Rigoletto?</i>
                   <i> Rigoletto?</i>

19:05.811 --> 19:07.778
    Yes, and what key
     do you sing at?
                       F.

19:07.780 --> 19:09.013
                    HENNESSY: F.
                   TONY: Or a C.

19:09.015 --> 19:10.481
          F or C?
                       G.

19:11.684 --> 19:13.683
   Uh, he has a fantastic range,
           Mr. Hennessy.

19:13.685 --> 19:15.820
I promise you,
 this will be

19:15.822 --> 19:17.988
           an experience
        you'll never forget.

19:17.990 --> 19:19.156
             Well, come with me,
                    major.

19:19.158 --> 19:20.291
                  Yes.

19:20.293 --> 19:21.725
      This is going to be
         an experience

19:21.727 --> 19:22.960
  none of us will ever forget.

19:22.962 --> 19:24.395
   What?
       Oh, nothing, sir.

19:24.397 --> 19:25.896
   Excuse me.

19:28.368 --> 19:32.436
            <i> [ACCORDION PLAYING]</i>

19:32.438 --> 19:33.904
Major Healey!

19:33.906 --> 19:36.106
    Oh!
            Shh!

19:36.108 --> 19:38.576
Oh, I am so happy
to see you.

19:38.578 --> 19:40.878
   Really? Gee, it's nice
  to know you been missed.

19:40.880 --> 19:43.447
Well, I-- I have been dying
to know when my birthday is.

19:43.449 --> 19:45.382
  Yeah, I bet you have.
  Sorry about the delay.

19:45.384 --> 19:47.685
Well, it does not matter now.
When is it, Major Healey?

19:47.687 --> 19:49.953
   Remember I told you the month
      was the title of a song?

19:49.955 --> 19:50.954
              [APPLAUSE OVER TV]

19:50.956 --> 19:53.023
You'll just love your birthday.

19:53.025 --> 19:54.358
    Uh-huh.
                   It's on...

19:54.360 --> 19:56.360
<i> And now, ladies and gentlemen,</i>
       <i> in just a moment,</i>

19:56.362 --> 19:58.329
       <i> we'll switch you</i>
  <i> from Hickam Field in Hawaii</i>

19:58.331 --> 20:02.065
  <i> to Cape Kennedy in Florida,</i>
   <i> and Major Anthony Nelson.</i>

20:02.067 --> 20:05.703
Oh, they're getting
ready for my master.

20:05.705 --> 20:06.703
         Um, this is your music.

20:06.705 --> 20:07.971
           Yeah.

20:07.973 --> 20:09.973
         And now, watch for
   the red light on that camera.

20:09.975 --> 20:12.243
   And that's the stage manager.
      He'll give you your cue.

20:12.245 --> 20:14.211
Ah, oh, listen, uh,
believe me, I'm not ready.

20:14.213 --> 20:15.446
Honestly, I'm not.

20:15.448 --> 20:17.414
        Oh, now, there's nothing
          to be nervous about.

20:21.053 --> 20:22.119
        The microphone!

20:24.157 --> 20:25.589
                Oh.

20:25.591 --> 20:29.293
You know, this--
     I hope I didn't break that.

20:29.295 --> 20:30.894
  There's nothing
to be nervous about.

20:30.896 --> 20:33.164
      Now, look, you have
an eight bar introduction here.

20:33.166 --> 20:34.798
I will be playing
  on the piano.
                    Yeah.

20:34.800 --> 20:36.600
 And you come
in right there.
                   Yeah.

20:36.602 --> 20:39.603
And when you come in there, you
be sure you take that camera.

20:39.605 --> 20:41.272
                  Yeah.
  And then-- Oh!

20:43.209 --> 20:44.908
That's it-- That's--
 That's all right.

20:44.910 --> 20:46.877
I have another copy.

20:46.879 --> 20:49.480
        Jeannie, you've got
   to do something. Look at him.

20:49.482 --> 20:50.681
What can I do?

20:50.683 --> 20:52.249
             Well, give him back
               Caruso's voice.

20:52.251 --> 20:53.250
  I want to.

20:53.252 --> 20:54.751
But I promised him
that I would not.

20:54.753 --> 20:56.854
         TV ANNOUNCER:
   <i> And now, to Cape Kennedy</i>

20:56.856 --> 20:59.156
   <i> and Major Anthony Nelson.</i>

21:01.227 --> 21:03.828
           [PLAYS VERDI'S
   "LA DONNA È MOBILE" ON PIANO]

21:06.532 --> 21:08.899
          [WHISPERING]
 Excuse me, can I look at this?

21:08.901 --> 21:10.434
    [HENNESSY STARTS PIECE OVER]

21:15.774 --> 21:18.042
               [HENNESSY REPEATS
                 THE SAME BAR]

21:21.114 --> 21:22.112
             You gotta help him.

21:22.114 --> 21:23.380
    [HENNESSY STARTS PIECE OVER]

21:23.382 --> 21:25.349
   H-how can I?
I gave him my word.

21:25.351 --> 21:27.418
         Look at the poor devil.

21:27.420 --> 21:28.752
              [WHISPERING]
               Excuse me.

21:31.057 --> 21:33.257
    [HENNESSY STARTS PIECE OVER]

21:34.493 --> 21:36.594
              Oh, I can't watch.

21:36.596 --> 21:38.161
Poor Major Nelson.

21:38.163 --> 21:41.232
How does he get himself
into these things?

21:44.636 --> 21:46.803
Major Healey.
                       Yeah.

21:46.805 --> 21:49.173
I promised him that he would
not sing like Caruso again.

21:49.175 --> 21:50.207
                      I know.

21:50.209 --> 21:51.208
But I did not promise

21:51.210 --> 21:54.211
that he would not sing
like anyone else!

21:54.213 --> 21:56.180
    Huh?

21:56.182 --> 21:57.848
         [MAGIC BOINGS]

21:57.850 --> 21:59.783
                   Now!
    Oh! All right.

22:03.055 --> 22:05.055
    [HENNESSY STARTS PIECE OVER]

