         [MAGIC BOINGS]

22:21.473 --> 22:24.341
    [HENNESSY STARTS PIECE OVER]

22:24.343 --> 22:27.278
       [DEEP MALE VOICE]
     ♪<i> La donna é mobile</i> ♪

22:27.280 --> 22:30.181
    ♪<i> Qual piuma al vento</i> ♪

22:30.183 --> 22:32.149
       ♪<i> Muto d'accento</i> ♪

22:32.151 --> 22:33.883
                I don't think
            that's right either.

22:33.885 --> 22:34.884
       Oh?

22:34.886 --> 22:37.787
       ♪<i> E di pensiero</i> ♪

22:37.789 --> 22:39.223
         [MAGIC BOINGS]

22:39.225 --> 22:41.925
     [NORMAL FEMALE VOICE]
     ♪<i> La donna é mobile</i> ♪

22:41.927 --> 22:44.728
    ♪<i> Qual piuma al vento</i> ♪

22:44.730 --> 22:48.532
       ♪<i> Muto d'accento</i> ♪

22:48.534 --> 22:51.368
       ♪<i> E di pensiero</i> ♪

22:54.540 --> 22:55.906
         [MAGIC BOINGS]

22:55.908 --> 22:57.508
      [BETTY BOOP'S VOICE]
       ♪<i> E di pensiero</i> ♪

22:57.510 --> 22:59.176
       ♪ Boop-Oop-A-Doop ♪

23:01.013 --> 23:03.013
             [♪♪♪]

23:09.755 --> 23:12.756
         [ALL LAUGHING]

23:12.758 --> 23:14.357
             ROGER:
  That's the Boop-Oop-A-Doop.

23:14.359 --> 23:16.760
   That's the funniest thing
 I ever heard in my whole life!

23:16.762 --> 23:18.662
             Oh! I tell you,
         I almost died laughing.

23:18.664 --> 23:20.197
                Major Healey,
            when is my birthday?

23:20.199 --> 23:22.199
           And the thing
   that breaks me up is you won!

23:22.201 --> 23:23.433
 [CHUCKLING]
Yeah, I know.

23:23.435 --> 23:24.868
What did it say
on the trophy?

23:24.870 --> 23:27.437
"For the most versatile voice
of the century."

23:27.439 --> 23:28.872
           And my birthday, huh?

23:28.874 --> 23:32.275
  You sang notes that haven't
   even been invented before.

23:32.277 --> 23:34.277
Oh, I'm sorry I couldn't
bring the trophy home,

23:34.279 --> 23:36.180
but, uh, General Peterson
was very adamant.

23:36.182 --> 23:37.981
He wanted to keep it
at the Officers' Club.

23:37.983 --> 23:39.382
               That's all right.
                He may have it.

23:39.384 --> 23:41.251
           Major Healey, please!
            When is my birthday?

23:41.253 --> 23:42.820
       Oh, your birthday,
        your birthday--

23:42.822 --> 23:43.921
Hey, when is her birthday?

23:43.923 --> 23:45.122
          Oh, listen.
        I've got a clue.

23:45.124 --> 23:46.824
        Only this time,
    we're gonna play a game.

23:46.826 --> 23:48.192
Ah! We're gonna play charades--

23:48.194 --> 23:49.326
                          No.
      No!

23:49.328 --> 23:50.694
                         No!
     Now, the first word--

23:50.696 --> 23:51.695
       It's a long word--

23:54.066 --> 23:56.500
          April first!
  Your birthday's April first!

23:56.502 --> 23:58.268
           April first. Oh, what
             a lovely birthday.

23:58.270 --> 23:59.570
            Oh, Jeannie,
          these are sharp.

23:59.572 --> 24:00.738
         I was only kidding.

24:00.740 --> 24:02.940
   Oh, April's my favorite month
            of the year!

24:02.942 --> 24:04.942
             [♪♪♪]

24:06.278 --> 24:08.278
      [INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

